National Agriculture Day, also known as Ag Day, is a day to celebrate the essential role that agriculture plays in society. It is marked on March 20th and this year's theme is "Agriculture: Food for Life." Agriculture contributes to the economy and provides job opportunities for millions of Americans. President Donald Trump's Secretary of Agriculture, Sonny Perdue, has been actively listening to farmers and is working on legislative and policy changes to support rural prosperity. President Trump has made advancing the agriculture sector a priority, with initiatives such as bringing broadband infrastructure to rural communities and tax cuts for farmers. The administration recognizes the critical role of agriculture in the nation's future.